  <entry>
    <title>Font mechanics</title>
    <link rel="alternate" type="text/html" hreflang="en" href="http://texmacs.github.io/notes/docs/font-mechanics.html"/>
    <id>texmacs.github.io/notes/font-mechanics.tm:2025-01-03T23:34:58Z</id>
    <updated>2025-01-03T23:34:58Z</updated>
    <published>2025-01-03T23:35:47Z</published>
    <summary><concat>We describe the various mechanisms and features of
    TeXmacs font handling, from the user interface at the level of documents
    to the inner workings of the various fonts types at the level of the
    <verbatim>C++</verbatim> source code. TeXmacs implements sophisticate
    algorithms to allow the use a wide variety of fonts despite of the facts
    that they do not have all the necessary glyphs, especially those needed in
    the typesetting of technical documents.</concat></summary>
  </entry>
